<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="94">Two specimens, probably from the same field collection by Barter in 1859, are housed in K, with neither of them designated as the holo- or isotype. For this reason, we designate the specimen K000313101 as the lectotype and K000313102 as the isolectotype.</paragraph>
